<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Cur" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Cur,</orth> term of contempt for a dog: <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.3.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. II, 3, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. tgv 4.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.119" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 119</bibl> <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.3.5" default="NO" valid="yes">As I, 3, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 1.1.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. Ind. 1, 17.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.2.139" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 2, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A IV, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.146" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 146</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.391" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 391</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.120" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 3, 120</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 5.1.43" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 43</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.89" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 89</bibl> etc. Designating a particular species of dogs: <cit><quote>as hounds and greyhounds, mongrels, spaniels, --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 93</bibl></cit>.<lb />Used as a term of reproach for men: <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.1.46" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 1, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.3.18" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 3, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.56" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 1, 44</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.6.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 6, 107</bibl> etc.
